# Shared Schema Contract

- shared/event_schema.py and shared/event_schema.ts MUST stay in sync
- Any field added to the Python dataclass must be mirrored in the TypeScript interface
- Field names use snake_case in both Python and TypeScript (JSON wire format is snake_case)
- Severity is always: "critical" | "high" | "medium" | "low" | "clean"
- Protocol is always: "mcp" | "a2a"
- Direction is always: "request" | "response"
- Never add or remove fields without verbal coordination between Yugandhar and Ruthvik
- The Threat type must include: type, severity, detail, pattern, gemini_analysis
- The CrossfireEvent must include: id, timestamp, protocol, direction, server, method, params, threats, severity
